                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A European War 1939/295: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-26T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 26, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>269. Your 547, March 24, 3 p.m. The War Department concurs with your proposed
                    action but on the understanding that its approval <pb facs="1084" n="1072"
                        xml:id="pg_1072"/> in respect to the aviators presently interned is not to
                    be construed as the initiation of a policy for the immediate release of any
                    aviators, American or Axis, who in the future may make forced landings.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
